01:09:14.100 --> 01:09:18.670
&gt;&gt; Peter, any Prisonaire
stories you can share with us?

01:09:18.670 --> 01:09:19.970
&gt;&gt; Peter Guralnick:
I always liked --

01:09:19.970 --> 01:09:23.450
and the Prisonaires were this
group that was brought to Sam

01:09:23.450 --> 01:09:29.090 position:56%
by his sometime partner, Jim
Bullet, who had had the Bullet label

01:09:29.090 --> 01:09:34.110
in Nashville which had one of
the greatest hits of all time

01:09:34.110 --> 01:09:37.760
in Francis Craig's
Near You in the 40's.

01:09:37.760 --> 01:09:40.790 position:56%
Something which I doubt that many of
you heard, and I wouldn't have heard

01:09:40.790 --> 01:09:42.520
if I weren't writing the book.

01:09:42.520 --> 01:09:47.460
But anyway, Jim Bullet brought
the Prisonaires who were part

01:09:47.460 --> 01:09:50.400
of the Frank Clemmons, Governor
Frank Clemmons, who was a great --

01:09:50.400 --> 01:09:54.430
Sam greatly admired as a true
Democrat, big D, little D,

01:09:54.430 --> 01:09:58.060
which Sam always considered
himself and a great believer

01:09:58.060 --> 01:10:01.580 position:56%
in rehabilitation prisons in prison.

01:10:01.580 --> 01:10:05.430
And Prisonaires had been appearing
on a number of radio shows

01:10:05.430 --> 01:10:08.360
in Nashville, had made
some [inaudible]

01:10:08.360 --> 01:10:11.350
and so that's how Sam heard them.

01:10:11.350 --> 01:10:14.550
Sam said, "Then the
devastation came over me."

01:10:14.550 --> 01:10:15.850
That's the quote I always liked.

01:10:15.850 --> 01:10:17.510
Sometimes I'll remember
the word devastation.

01:10:17.510 --> 01:10:18.920
Sometimes I don't.

01:10:18.920 --> 01:10:22.540
Because it was both the music
which was very much derived

01:10:22.540 --> 01:10:24.340
from the Ink Spots
which was really --

01:10:24.340 --> 01:10:29.490
Bill Kenny, an idol of Elvis'
as well as the lead singer

01:10:29.490 --> 01:10:34.180
for the Prisonaires,
but Johnny Brag.

01:10:34.180 --> 01:10:39.370
But it was also the idea of
doing something, of being a kind

01:10:39.370 --> 01:10:43.150 position:56%
of Clarence Darrell, doing something
that could lead to rehabilitation.

01:10:43.150 --> 01:10:44.450
And he went over.

01:10:44.450 --> 01:10:49.000
He went over to Nashville to
meet with Frank Clemmons to try

01:10:49.000 --> 01:10:51.530
to pursuade him not to allow
Sam to record them in prison,

01:10:51.530 --> 01:10:55.990
which he could have easily done,
but to allow them to be transported

01:10:55.990 --> 01:10:59.920
