the Sun Studio in Memphis.

01:10:59.920 --> 01:11:02.430
Memphis Recording Service
in Memphis.

01:11:02.430 --> 01:11:07.630
And he brought with him a gospel
singer named Howard Surat [assumed

01:11:07.630 --> 01:11:10.660 position:56%
spelling] who Sam often said had the
most beautiful voice he ever heard.

01:11:10.660 --> 01:11:14.060
Again, Sam had [inaudible]
for everyone.

01:11:14.060 --> 01:11:15.360
That was his [inaudible].

01:11:15.360 --> 01:11:16.930
But he is a beautiful singer,

01:11:16.930 --> 01:11:20.200
and Sam tried very half-heartedly
to get him to sing pop.

01:11:20.200 --> 01:11:23.350
And I think was very relieved
when Howard Surat had no interest.

01:11:23.350 --> 01:11:26.360
Well, he was convinced
that if Frank Clemmons

01:11:26.360 --> 01:11:33.690
who was also an Evangelical -- if
